gpt-message.content:
Internal signals and their explanation is as follows: 
Internal signals: 

1. tri0 areset;
2. tri0 [1:0] inclk;
3. reg pll_lock_sync;
4. wire [4:0] wire_pll1_clk;
5. wire wire_pll1_fbout;
6. wire wire_pll1_locked;

Explanation:

1. areset: This signal is defined as an input tri-state with default "off" state. In the current module, it is used to asynchronously reset the PLL configuration.

2. inclk: This signal is a 2-bit tri-state bus used as the source input clock for the PLL. It represents the clock signal that will be manipulated by the PLL module to generate a new clock signal.

3. pll_lock_sync: This is a registered binary signal that is used to synchronize the locked state of the PLL with the asynchronous reset condition. It is reset when 'areset' signal is high and set when 'wire_pll1_locked' has a positive edge. 

4. wire_pll1_clk: This is a 5-bit wide internal signal used as the new clock signal generated by PLL. It is connected to the clk output of the module.

5. wire_pll1_fbout: This is an internal feedback output signal of the PLL, used for feedback mechanism of PLL's operation.

6. wire_pll1_locked: This is an internal wire that represents whether the PLL has achieved and maintained a lock on the desired frequency. It is connected to the locked output of this module and also used to drive the pll_lock_sync.

